      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>When an unsymmetrical alkene such as propene is treated with <i>N</i>-bromosuccinimide in aqueous dimethyl sulfoxide, the major product has the bromine atom bonded to the less highly substituted carbon atom. Is this Markovnikov or non-Markovnikov orientation? (Section 7.8) Explain.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa0VTIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--675f193f0abf54683fb2110bb3f9d9c3eec4aedf/OChem_08_03_005.jpg\" alt=\"A reaction shows propene reacting with molecular bromine in the presence of water to form bromo-2-propanol.\">",
